fields.name: key
fields.doc: The object key name (or key) that uniquely identifies the object in the bucket.

fields.name: sequence_number
fields.doc:
The sequence number, which is an ordinal that's included in the records for a given
object. To order records of the same bucket and key, you can sort on sequence_number.
For a given bucket and key, a lexicographically larger sequence_number implies that the
record was introduced to the bucket more recently.

fields.name: version_id
fields.doc:
The object's version ID. When you enable versioning on a bucket, Amazon S3 assigns a
version number to objects that are added to the bucket. Objects that are stored in your
bucket before you set the versioning state have a version ID of null.

fields.name: is_delete_marker
fields.doc:
The object's delete marker status. If the object is a delete marker, this value is True.
Otherwise, it's False.

fields.name: size
fields.doc:
The object size in bytes, not including the size of incomplete multipart uploads or
object metadata. If is_delete_marker is True, the size is 0.

fields.name: last_modified_date
fields.doc: The object creation date or the last modified date, whichever is the latest.

fields.name: e_tag
fields.doc:
The entity tag (ETag), which is a hash of the object. The ETag reflects changes only to
the contents of an object, not to its metadata.

fields.name: storage_class
fields.doc: The storage class that's used for storing the object.

fields.name: is_multipart
fields.doc:
The object's upload type. If the object was uploaded as a multipart upload, this value
is True. Otherwise, it's False.

fields.name: encryption_status
fields.doc:
The object's server-side encryption status, depending on what kind of encryption key is
used. If the object isn't encrypted, the value is null.

fields.name: is_bucket_key_enabled
fields.doc:
The object's S3 Bucket Key enablement status. If the object uses an S3 Bucket Key for
SSE-KMS, this value is True. Otherwise, it's False.

fields.name: kms_key_arn
fields.doc:
The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the KMS key with which the object is encrypted, for
rows where encryption_status is SSE-KMS or DSSE-KMS. If the object isn't encrypted with
SSE-KMS or DSSE-KMS, the value is null. Note: If a row represents an object version that
no longer existed at the time that a delete or overwrite event was processed,
kms_key_arn contains a null value, even if the encryption_status column value is SSE-KMS
or DSSE-KMS.

fields.name: checksum_algorithm
fields.doc:
The algorithm thatâ€™s used to create the checksum for the object. If no checksum is
present, this value is null.

fields.name: object_tags
fields.doc:
The object tags that are associated with the object. Object tags are stored as a map of
key-value pairs. If an object has no object tags, an empty map ("{}") is stored.

fields.name: user_metadata
fields.doc:
The user metadata that's associated with the object. User metadata is stored as a map of
key-value pairs. If an object has no user metadata, an empty map ("{}") is stored.
